<subSubSection id="2DB1AFBD5C8092226FB12F72A0113D3F" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="F48680B8DE01467196C9F057380E664A" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D026EA2A93A33D592DE263487426C1DD" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
We categorized this species as Endangered (criteria EN) according to B1 (EOO &lt;5000 km2) and B2ab (ii, iii) (AOO &lt;500 km2) from 
<bibRefCitation id="306EA3DD9459BC6D108D77591536D63B" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Spring Lake Publishing, Spring Lake, Utah" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B13" refString="IUCN, 2019. Guidelines for using the IUCN red list categories and criteria. Version 14. Standards and Petitions Committee. http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" title="Guidelines for using the IUCN red list categories and criteria. Version 14. Standards and Petitions Committee." url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2019">IUCN (2019)</bibRefCitation>
. Although populations of 
<taxonomicName id="2D2CF0CA67BB6AC3A5C851ABA7361DDD" genus="I." lsidName="I. maranhensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="maranhensis">
<emphasis id="B4C749339B8DA17049A60D0404BB61F5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">I. maranhensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occur in protected areas, this species is threatened due to the reduction of its habitat because of anthropogenic fires lit by small communities who remove vegetation with fire for subsistence agriculture in the Cerrado 
<emphasis id="2BF257D1B6270FC931A065E662103394" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">sensu stricto</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="3EB1AE1030C97E45B78E2209142899C5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<normalizedToken id="5A57B6B0F645D11B899D045EE54DEB9C" originalValue="Cerradão">Cerradao</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
formations (
<bibRefCitation id="334A264666A40B56AEF8F0230A0A3D3C" author="Ribeiro, JR" editor="Sano, SM" journalOrPublisher="Embrapa, Brasilia" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="151 - 212" refId="B31" refString="Ribeiro, JR, Walter, BMT, 2008. As principais fitofisionomias Cerrado. In: Sano, SM, Almeida, SP, Ribeiro, JF, Eds., Cerrado: Ecologia e Flora. Embrapa, Brasilia: 151 - 212" title="As principais fitofisionomias Cerrado." volumeTitle="Cerrado: Ecologia e Flora." year="2008">Ribeiro and Walter 2008</bibRefCitation>
). According to Estivalet (1997), prostrate or climbing plants seem to be more prone to burning than upright species, whose growth points are more protected inside the clump.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
